		<title>Cilantro-Lime Salad Dressing</title>
	</head>
	<body>
		<Section>
		<div id="heading">
			<h1 id="title">Cilantro-Lime Salad Dressing</h1>
			<h3>Makes 6 Servings (1 1/4 Cup Total)</h3>
		</div>	
		</Section>
		<section>	
		<div id=nutr>
			<h2><em>Nutrition</em></h2>		
				<p><strong>Per tablespoon:</strong> 53 calories; 6 g fat (1 g sat, 4 g mono); 0 mg cholesterol; 1 g carbohydrates; 0 g protein; 0 g fibre; 59 mg sodium; 14 mg potassium.
				</p>
		</div>		
		</section>	
		<section>
		<div id="ing">
		<h2>Ingredients</h2>
				<p>
					<ul>
						<li><em>1 cup</em> packed cilantro</li>
						<li><em>1/2 cup</em> extra-virgin olive oil</li>
						<li><em>1/4 cup</em> lime juice</li>
						<li><em>1/4 cup</em> orange juice</li>
						<li><em>1/2 teaspoon</em> salt</li>
						<li><em>1/2 teaspoon</em> black pepper</li>
						<li><em>1 Pinch</em> minced garlic</li>	
					</ul>	
				</p>
		</div>		
		</section>	
		<section>
		<div id="prep">
			<h2>Preparation</h2>	
				<p>
					<ol>
						<li>Using food processor (e.g. standard blender or magic bullet) blend cilantro and garlic until pureed.</li>	
						<li>Add oil, lime juice, and orange juice to puree mix and blend until smooth</li>
						<li>Add salt and pepper, to taste.</li>
						<li>Use immediately, or portion into storage containers and freeze for future use.</li>
					</ol>	
				</p>
		</div>
		</section>
